@Styromaniac: the best thing to help avoiding such conversations would be to ignore the whole incident, not arguing that no point could have been made

>Nobody, not even Badoolove, could convince oneself they did right by posting CP.

People easily convince themselves they did right (or at least, nothing wrong) while actually doing wrong from others' viewpoint. Ultimately, one can claim "what's good to me is right" and your ethics will be irrelevant to them

@Pexo: dunno, i'm only theorizing from reading discussion and the fact that it's hard to be unaware of possible consequences of posting CP

@Styromaniac: this can't possibly be novel and indeed it isn't. Both ascinema and showterm (haven't research much, but there are also *tons* of others) date back to early 2010s, but as can be seen from [showterm](https://showterm.io) credits block, this is just webification of old tools

> 2000-12-27: ttyrec 1.0 Released
> The script command appeared in 3.0BSD.

@Styromaniac: if you want a personal solution, you can open VLC manually, i guess. But as universal it won't work for those who don't have it installed

***

I don't think you need to bother with files for that. Local storage api should work, it's just that somebody has to write/edit the code instead of just using existing player as is

@Styromaniac:

> The bandwidth of the data exfiltration can't go that high overseas

That's a very weak argument. They could easily use servers or botnet located in US

@Styromaniac: there are all kinds of vaccines , made with different technologies by different manufacturers... not every shot given with intent to create immunity to covid would even qualify to be called "vaccine" in later XX-early XXI century lingo . there is enough reasonable doubt about clinical tests and their validity (and sometimes shots are being given prior to results even being published) for some of "vaccines"

---

i'm pretty sure there's more risk in getting infected than in getting vaccine , but governments and/or vaccine makers have incentive to present vaccine risks less than they are . safety of population (which most governments would at least try to certain extent to protect) is not the same thing as safety of individual (and priority of that easily fades to negligible values) . sorry for broading the topic
